{"id":49601,"date":"2021-11-09T00:00:00","date_gmt":"2021-11-09T05:00:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/11\/09\/holiday-ppc-mistakes"},"modified":"2023-10-17T10:30:19","modified_gmt":"2023-10-17T15:30:19","slug":"holiday-ppc-mistakes","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/11\/09\/holiday-ppc-mistakes","title":{"rendered":"8 Perilous PPC Mistakes to Avoid This Holiday Season"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"tag__text\">Your food is bought, family and friends have been invited, and gifts are wrapped. You may think you\u2019re a holiday pro until you log online to find your PPC account in shambles!<\/div>\n<div><\/div>\n<div data-embed-button=\"images\" data-entity-embed-display=\"view_mode:media.simple_image\" data-entity-type=\"media\" data-entity-uuid=\"4a252561-6915-48d8-8bed-179800e93720\" data-langcode=\"en\" class=\"embedded-entity align-center\">\n<article>\n<div><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/holiday-ppc-mistakes-the-office-christmas-party.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" alt=\"holiday ppc mistakes: the office christmas party\" typeof=\"foaf:Image\" class=\"aligncenter\" \/><\/div>\n<div><\/div>\n<\/article>\n<\/div>\n<p>With this season being such an important time for countless businesses, you don\u2019t want to fall victim to any PPC mistakes when it comes to your holiday marketing. \u2018Tis the season to remember common <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2023\/10\/10\/holiday-ppc-advertising-lead-gen\">holiday PPC<\/a>\u00a0pitfalls\u2014and how to dodge them.<\/p>\n<p>I\u2019m going to share my tips on how you can turn these holiday perils into holiday presents your account will be eager to unwrap.<\/p>\n<h2>1. Ramping up your spend a little <em>too<\/em> much<\/h2>\n<p>Your<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2017\/10\/17\/holiday-marketing-ideas\"> <\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2017\/10\/17\/holiday-marketing-ideas\">holiday marketing<\/a> ramp up doesn\u2019t mean you have to go overboard with raising <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2013\/08\/29\/ppc-budget-guide\">your PPC budgets<\/a>. While in some industries bid prices have been known to increase as high as <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2017\/11\/27\/holiday-marketing-stats\">140% <\/a>over their yearly average during the holidays, don\u2019t let this scare you into raising your bids and budget beyond your means.<\/p>\n<p>Think of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2020\/10\/08\/holiday-advertising-best-practices-2020\">your holiday PPC campaigns<\/a> as you would a sport: you can be the most in-shape person in the world, but you\u2019ll lose the game if you lack the necessary skills. In this case, your budget is your fitness level and your strategy is your skill level. Your budget can only take you so far in PPC, but <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2014\/04\/24\/ppc-performance\">your optimization strategy<\/a> is what will bring home the trophy.<\/p>\n<p>With increased demand and heightened competition, you may find raising your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2013\/11\/26\/holiday-promotions\">holiday PPC budget<\/a> a must-do. That\u2019s completely reasonable, but being cautious with it can save you from wasting PPC spend.<\/p>\n<h2>2. Putting all your PPC budget into one tactic<\/h2>\n<p>I should have put a warning in the beginning that there will be a lot of anecdotal analogies in this post. As the saying goes, don\u2019t put all your eggs in one basket.<\/p>\n<p>During the off-season, you may have one \u201ctried and true strategy\u201d that works for your account. However, since holiday customers will be everywhere across their devices this season, a <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/what-is-multichannel-marketing\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">multichannel strategy <\/a>is the best option for PPC success.<\/p>\n<p>Not only will you want<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/08\/02\/ppc-strategies\"> other PPC strategies<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/08\/02\/ppc-strategies\"> <\/a>running in case one tactic falls short, but you\u2019ll also want to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2013\/10\/15\/multi-channel-marketing\">maximize your PPC opportunities across channels.<\/a><\/p>\n<div data-embed-button=\"images\" data-entity-embed-display=\"view_mode:media.simple_image\" data-entity-type=\"media\" data-entity-uuid=\"763588dd-8fd8-4f60-89c8-64d2476e5610\" data-langcode=\"en\" class=\"embedded-entity align-center\">\n<article>\n<div><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/online-advertising-ppc-channels.png\" width=\"720\" height=\"480\" alt=\"list of online advertising PPC channels\" typeof=\"foaf:Image\" class=\"aligncenter\" \/><\/div>\n<div><\/div>\n<\/article>\n<\/div>\n<h2>3. Not running ads on mobile<\/h2>\n<p>A <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2014\/10\/16\/mobile-ppc-strategy\">mobile PPC strategy<\/a> is a holiday strategy that will ensure you capture every potential customer this season.<\/p>\n<p>It&#8217;s no secret that all PPC channels have huge mobile audiences, and that matters even more so during the holiday season. In fact, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2017\/11\/27\/holiday-marketing-stats\">64%<\/a> of smartphone shoppers turn to mobile search before heading to a store, and 76% of mobile shoppers change their mind about which brand they choose after searching online.<\/p>\n<p>A <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/mobile-marketing-strategies\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">mobile marketing strategy<\/a> for the holidays should include <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/07\/06\/how-to-write-copy-that-sells#concisecopy\">clear and concise ad copy<\/a> and landing pages that look good on a mobile screen. Also, try taking your<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2013\/08\/19\/what-is-mobile-marketing\"> <\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2013\/08\/19\/what-is-mobile-marketing\">mobile marketing<\/a> a step further by bidding up on mobile devices, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2018\/08\/30\/mastering-display-placements\">placing display ads on apps<\/a>, or implementing campaigns specifically for mobile devices.<\/p>\n<div data-embed-button=\"images\" data-entity-embed-display=\"view_mode:media.simple_image\" data-entity-type=\"media\" data-entity-uuid=\"ca782f2c-76da-4e56-addd-19c6f993c0d6\" data-langcode=\"en\" class=\"embedded-entity align-center\">\n<article>\n<div><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/holiday-ppc-mistakes-search-ad-example-with-holiday-copy.png\" width=\"281\" height=\"500\" alt=\"holiday ppc mistakes: mobile-friendly search ad\" typeof=\"foaf:Image\" class=\"aligncenter\" \/><\/div>\n<\/article>\n<\/div>\n<h2>4. Not being inclusive<\/h2>\n<p>This holds true for all of your <a href=\"\/blog\/ws\/2021\/11\/05\/december-marketing-ideas\">December marketing ideas<\/a>. This year and beyond, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/04\/28\/diversity-in-marketing\">diversity and inclusion in PPC<\/a> should be a given when considering the holiday season.<\/p>\n<p>For example, <a href=\"https:\/\/welcomesoftware.com\/insights\/inclusive-marketing\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">70%<\/a> of millennials (a large PPC demographic) are more likely to choose one brand over another if that brand demonstrates inclusion and diversity in its promotional offers\u2014even if the viewer themselves does not identify with that demographic.<\/p>\n<p>If you want to make the most out of your PPC this season, your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2020\/11\/5\/accessibility-inclusivity-advertising\">ad copy and creative assets should be inclusive<\/a> of all cultures and winter holidays.<\/p>\n<div data-embed-button=\"images\" data-entity-embed-display=\"view_mode:media.simple_image\" data-entity-type=\"media\" data-entity-uuid=\"4f2599f8-7dea-4b95-a8b0-369c14d82e11\" data-langcode=\"en\" class=\"embedded-entity align-center\">\n<article>\n<div><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/holiday-ppc-mistakes-diversity-inclusion-ad.jpg\" width=\"720\" height=\"405\" alt=\"holiday ppc mistakes: inclusive ad creative\" typeof=\"foaf:Image\" class=\"aligncenter\" \/><\/div>\n<\/article>\n<\/div>\n<p class=\"text-align-center\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.advocate.com\/business\/2020\/11\/11\/ritz-crackers-spreads-some-joy-lgbtq-inclusive-ads\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Image source<\/em><\/a><\/p>\n<p>We have plenty of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/11\/16\/inclusive-holiday-marketing-ideas\">inclusive holiday marketing ideas<\/a> here to inspire you.<\/p>\n<h2>5. Trying something a little<em> too<\/em> new<\/h2>\n<p>Cosmetologists preach to brides and grooms to not try anything new the week of their wedding. The same goes for PPC\u2014high-traffic holiday times aren\u2019t ideal for trying a strategy you\u2019re not 100% confident in.<\/p>\n<p>If you want to branch out into <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/01\/04\/best-marketing-strategies-2021\">exciting n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/01\/04\/best-marketing-strategies-2021\">ew strategies<\/a> during this time, start small with a low-risk budget and a back up plan in place. Be sure to research beforehand to see how similar strategies have performed during this time in your industry. It also wouldn\u2019t hurt to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/03\/15\/google-ads-account-audit-post-covid\">audit your account<\/a> to understand your holiday performance in past years, so your expectations land in a reasonable spot for a new strategy. This is particularly important for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/11\/04\/b2b-holiday-marketing-ideas\">B2B holiday marketing<\/a>, which can oftentimes be slow.<\/p>\n<h2>6. Landing page outages<\/h2>\n<p>The last thing you need during this peak season is for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2013\/11\/27\/seasonal-landing-pages\">your holiday landing page<\/a> to pop up with errors. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/08\/10\/content-audit#landingpage\">Run a landing page audit<\/a> to make sure it\u2019s good to run through the holidays. That could include practices like<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2013\/07\/11\/landing-page-conversion-rate-guide\"> <\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2013\/07\/11\/landing-page-conversion-rate-guide\">testing out your forms<\/a> or purchase processes, adjusting copy to be clear and concise, and checking for any possible fires before you need to put them out.<\/p>\n<div data-embed-button=\"images\" data-entity-embed-display=\"view_mode:media.simple_image\" data-entity-type=\"media\" data-entity-uuid=\"afc8865e-ba8b-4c99-8c08-e80dc691dcd5\" data-langcode=\"en\" class=\"embedded-entity align-center\">\n<article>\n<div><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/holiday-ppc-mistakes-landing-page-example.jpeg\" width=\"720\" height=\"352\" alt=\"holiday ppc mistakes: landing page example\" typeof=\"foaf:Image\" \/><\/div>\n<\/article>\n<\/div>\n<p class=\"text-align-center\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/resources\/2021-holiday-marketing-guide\/?itm_source=other&amp;itm_medium=internal%20share&amp;itm_campaign=2021%20resource&amp;itm_content=holiday%20guide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Image source<\/em><\/a><\/p>\n<h2>7. Account disapprovals or holds<\/h2>\n<p>With <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/07\/28\/google-ads-three-strikes-policy-program#:~:text=What%20is%20Google's%20three%2Dstrike,resulting%20in%20indefinite%20account%20suspension.\">Google\u2019s recent 3-strike policy update<\/a> for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/06\/23\/google-ads-disapprovals\">ad disapprovals<\/a>, your radar for potential disapprovals should be on high alert. Even if you aren\u2019t in a high-risk industry, double-check your ads for any grammatical errors, mismatching links, or poor ad strength.<\/p>\n<p>Aside from your ads getting taken down, having your entire account put on a hold during the holidays would be even worse. In your account, navigate to the billing section and ensure that your payment information is up to date.<\/p>\n<p>In my experience, I\u2019ve seen many accounts go down due to credit card limit issues as well. Be sure your form of payment has a threshold that meets your high holiday spend.<\/p>\n<h2>8. Using the same ad copy you would normally<\/h2>\n<p>\u2018Tis the season to spice up your ads! Take advantage of this festive time of year to give your audience something fresh to look at.\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/joinative.com\/holiday-ads-tips\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">50%<\/a> of consumers say holiday ads impact their purchasing decisions. If you\u2019re not running a holiday-specific ad, you\u2019re missing out on the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2020\/11\/10\/boost-holiday-sales-and-revenue\">influential power on sales the holidays have<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>The holidays are an exciting time for many, and you can show your brand\u2019s fun side with <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2021\/11\/01\/holiday-copywriting\">authentic and emotional holiday copywriting<\/a>. For example, try sprinkling in<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2013\/11\/25\/ultimate-holiday-text-ad\"> festive language into a text ad<\/a>, or swap out your brand colors for holiday colors on a display ad.<\/p>\n<p>However your business chooses to celebrate the season, it\u2019s sure to be well-received by an antsy holiday audience.<\/p>\n<div data-embed-button=\"images\" data-entity-embed-display=\"view_mode:media.simple_image\" data-entity-type=\"media\" data-entity-uuid=\"cfba7e5d-0027-4cb1-bc95-b341dfb8575d\" data-langcode=\"en\" class=\"embedded-entity align-center\">\n<article>\n<div><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/holiday-ppc-mistakes-ultimate-holiday-text-ad.png\" width=\"628\" height=\"294\" alt=\"great example of holiday ppc text ad\" typeof=\"foaf:Image\" \/><\/div>\n<\/article>\n<\/div>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>Turn these PPC mistakes into holiday marketing wins!<\/h2>\n<p>Think these holiday PPC mistakes are unavoidable? Think again! To recap, here our tips to turn these woes into<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2015\/10\/15\/holiday-marketing-tips\"> holiday marketing wins:<\/a><\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Raise your bids and budget only when necessary.<\/li>\n<li>Run a multichannel PPC strategy.<\/li>\n<li>Make your holiday PPC campaigns\u00a0mobile-friendly.<\/li>\n<li>Make sure your ads are diverse and inclusive.<\/li>\n<li>Don\u2019t try anything new that you\u2019re not 100% comfortable with.<\/li>\n<li>Check your landing pages for any potential snags.<\/li>\n<li>Resolve any disapprovals or payment issues before the season starts.<\/li>\n<li>Use authentic (and cliche-free!) holiday copywriting<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>If you want to capitalize on increased consumer spending and engagement during the holidays, avoid these PPC mistakes\u2014like spending too much, neglecting inclusivity, ad disapprovals, and more!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":69,"featured_media":49844,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"ope